FBIS4-17452 "drsov079_s_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-079 Daily Report 23 Apr 1994 Georgia Russia Cancels Duties on Georgian Goods Russia Cancels Duties on Georgian Goods LD2304095094 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 0800 GMT 23 Apr 94 LD2304095094 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network Georgian BFN [Text] According to SAKINPORM, Georgia's customs department has received a letter from the Customs Committee of the Russian Federation signed by Kruglyakov, first deputy chairman of the committee. The letter says: Because the Republic of Georgia has been a member of the CIS since 1 March 1994, in accordance with the edict issued by the Russian Federation Customs Committee, the heads of its regional departments and customs houses have been officially instructed not to levy a tax in the form of VAT, special duties, and excise duties on goods produced in Georgia and carried from the Georgian territory retroactive to 1 March 1994. Money already paid for the above-mentioned taxes should be refunded from the customs house account or it can be applied to future payments.
